      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "rationale": "The primary QoI (normalised index of hemolysis, NIH) is the clinically accepted metric for pump-induced blood trauma and is directly linked to the regulatory acceptance criterion (RH < 1 relative to predicate). Secondary QoIs (wall shear stress, exposure time) are mechanistically connected to the power-law hemolysis model.",
