      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "rationale": "Validation experiments used the same FDA generic centrifugal pump geometry operated at flow rates and rotational speeds spanning the CPB operating envelope (2–6 L/min, 2000–3500 RPM). Blood analogue fluid (glycerol-water mixture) viscosity matched physiological range. Geometric and operational similarity to the COU is well-established.",
