      "factorStatus": "scoped-out",
      "rationale": "Numerical solver error (iterative convergence and round-off) is scoped out at MRL 2 for this COU. Residuals were monitored to below 1e-5 for all equations and mass imbalance confirmed below 0.01%, providing sufficient confidence that iterative error does not materially affect NIH predictions. Formal Gradation assessment is not required at MRL 2 per ASME V&V 40-2018 Table 3."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "scoped-out",
      "rationale": "Use error assessment is scoped out at MRL 2. The simulation was conducted by an engineer with documented CFD training and peer-reviewed by a second analyst. Simulation setup checklist and review records are archived in the project quality file. Formal use-error Gradation assessment is not required at MRL 2 per ASME V&V 40-2018 Table 3."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "scoped-out",
      "rationale": "Model form assessment (turbulence model selection, hemolysis power-law exponent uncertainty) is scoped out at MRL 2. Sensitivity of NIH predictions to turbulence model (k-omega SST vs. realizable k-epsilon) was informally evaluated and showed less than 8% variation, supporting the selected model form. Formal Gradation assessment not required at MRL 2."
